videos.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander throws up a 3-pointer as the shot clock expires and Wenyen Gabriel blocks a shot on the other end for the Wildcats.
videos.headline: Gilgeous-Alexander beats the shot clock with nice 3-pointer

videos.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander spins around a defender and then kicks it out to Kevin Knox who drains an open 3-pointer for Kentucky.
videos.headline: Gilgeous-Alexander sets up Knox's open 3-pointer

videos.description: Admiral Schofield draws contact on a 3-pointer for a potential 4-point play and Tennessee's bench loves it.
videos.headline: Schofield gives Vols life with big 3-pointer

videos.description: Kevin Knox turns the ball over and Jordan Bone finishes with a layup on the other end for Tennessee to tie the game.
videos.headline: Vols steal momentum on Bone's layup

videos.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander forces a turnover and draws contact on the layup for Kentucky.
videos.headline: Gilgeous-Alexander answers with steal-and-score

videos.description: The Wildcats force a turnover and Quade Green finds Kevin Knox on the other end for a lay-in.
videos.headline: Defense turns into sweet layup from Knox

videos.description: Lamonte Turner makes a long jumper to put the Vols back in the lead in the second half.
videos.headline: Turner sinks long 3-pointer for Tennessee

videos.description: Sacha Killeya-Jones grabs an offensive board and then slams it down with two hands to extend the Wildcats' lead.
videos.headline: Killeya-Jones throws down monster putback dunk in traffic

videos.description: Kentucky head coach John Calipari says despite all the adversity his team played together, which was key in winning the SEC tournament.
videos.headline: Calipari says Cats had to come together to win tourney

videos.description: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander says he has been building mental toughness since he was a kid, which helped him lead Kentucky's offense to a win over Tennessee.
videos.headline: Gilgeous-Alexander credits mental toughness after win

videos.description: Kentucky finds a way to beat Tennessee 77-72 to win the SEC tournament, guaranteeing their spot in the big dance.
videos.headline: Kentucky wins 4th straight SEC title
